cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the problem of learning the weights of a deep convolutional neural network. It also involves the development of an algorithm for simultaneously learning all the kernels from the training data. Additionally, it investigates the effectiveness of the proposed approach through numerical experiments. 

It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as convolutional neural networks are widely used in computer vision tasks such as image classification, object detection, and segmentation. 

Furthermore, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI and convolutional neural networks are a popular technique in deep learning. 

It may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper deals with the learning of neural networks. 

Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper proposes a new algorithm for learning the weights of a convolutional neural network.
